properties.title: The be-all and end-all in today's real estate marketing
properties.subTitle: The be-all and end-all in today's real estate marketing
properties.teaser_short: Today's real estate marketing. A variety of factors must be considered when marketing real estate in the digital age. But finding buyers is not necessarily more complicated. In the sales process, much is also in- between simpler and more efficient.

properties.text:
Current developments on the residential real estate market in Switzerland clearly show that demand has exceeded supply, and not just since the pandemic. Although there are still many interested parties in response to an ad for sale, potential sellers are increasingly adopting a wait-and-see attitude. Some have put on the handbrake and perhaps prefer to wait a little longer to see where the regional market and prices are heading - in the best case, further upwards.

New generations, new laws

Real estate agents in Switzerland are also noticing that the average holding period of a property is decreasing. Up-and-coming generations are moving away from the previously almost ironclad law of owning a house or apartment for a lifetime. In addition, there is a trend towards so-called off-market transactions. Real estate is being sold "under the table", as it were, and many a brokerage firm is working with internal lists. A special feature and at the same time a new trend are digital offer procedures, in which the property is passed on to the highest bidder in a bidding process.

In terms of renovation before sale, another important trend is emerging, as buyers often already anticipate investments in a possible conversion of the property when they purchase it. Existing owners should therefore not waste too much time and money on last-minute modernization of the property. New owners want to realize and implement their own wishes after the purchase. In general, of course, attention should be paid to the property in question and its condition, but it doesn't really make sense to completely renovate a classic single-family home before selling it. Costs and returns, i.e. a higher sales price, are not within acceptable limits.

Professional beauty corrections, such as repairing the parquet flooring in the living area, the tiles and joints in the bathroom and repainting the walls, can already achieve great effects with relatively little effort. The first inspection of a property offered for sale and the completeness of the documents or the property dossier of the house or apartment are particularly important. This includes the year of construction, exact address and detailed floor plans as well as information on heating and ancillary costs. In the case of condominiums, this also includes data on the renewal fund and investments made in previous years, and in the case of houses, details on the cubature and the exact size of the plot. Hiding glaring problems or not addressing them at the viewing is not wise from the broker's or the seller's point of view. Last but not least, when selling a property, the saying "the honest man is the fool" usually does not prove to be true.

How the marketing period can be shortened

Nowadays, the marketing time of a property can also be significantly shortened with the help of some digital solutions: These include, for example, the possibility of a virtual 360-degree tour or the visualization of the interiors of newly built properties. There are now a large number of digital tools available. For example, virtual "homestaging" to make an existing home aesthetically appealing and "palatable" to potential buyers. In the case of renovation projects, it may be worthwhile to use a before-and-after visualization to get a first impression of what the future property could look like. Videos of existing properties, including drone footage, are also becoming increasingly popular and widespread.

Another important aspect to consider in marketing is real estate advertisements: Large ad portals such as Homegate, ImmoScout24, Comparis or Newhome have regional strengths and weaknesses. Not every portal is equally well suited for different cities, regions or cantons. There are significant differences in reach and usage. In the end, the all-important question of the exact offer price remains. Here, the real estate agent has a very clear recommendation: the "price on request" that used to be advertised has definitely had its day in real estate marketing.
